definitions.definition: ( aviation ) A type of energy -absorbing landing gear strut in which sudden compression or extension of the strut causes a gas -filled chamber to push or pull a piston which forces oil through a small orifice , resulting in absorption of energy through viscous effects.
examples: If the oil leaks out of the oleos , they won't be able to cushion the aircraft against a hard landing.
